== Old English ==
*''Day of the Week:'' '''Saturday'''
**'''Last:''' [[Friday]]
**'''Next:''' [[Sunday]] (of next week)
----

===Declension===
*Singular: se Sæternesdæg, þæs Sæternesdæges, þǽm Sæternesdæge, þone Sæternesdæg
*Plural: þá Sæternesdagas, þǽra Sæternesdaga, þǽm Sæternesdagum, þá Sæternesdagas

===Etymology===
Old English ''Sætern(es)dæg'' from Latin ''Saturni dies'' (day of Saturn)
===Noun===
#The seventh [[day]] of the [[week]] in the USA.
#The sixth day of the week in Europe and in systems using the ISO 8601 norm.
#The Biblical seventh [[day]] of the [[week]], observed as [[Sabbath]] or "Day of Rest".
It follows [[Friday]] and precedes [[Sunday]].
#An appointment, person, or feeling associated with this day of the week.

